                                                                                         Jenkins

Note: Jenkins Mother Document (https://www.jenkins.io/doc/)
Requirements of Jenkins
  1. Resources 
      RAM & ROM
  2. Dependences
      Java installation

 Jenkins uses port :8080 
 Jenkins folder/path :/var/lib/jenkins

Info:
     Java application(human readable lang) ----------High level lang/compiled-----------> .class file(java binary file/machine readable code)
                                              ( javac is a compiler for java files)           ( Run .class file/binary file we need JVM)
                                                                                           |-------------------JRE--------------------------|
     |--------------------------------------------------- JDK( Java Development Kit) -------------------------------------------------------|

Imp: 
 INSTALLATION OF JENKINS
    1. Download JDK from oracle website or from Linux apt package manager
    2. Jenkins Java compactability ----> Java Support Policy ---> Select the version    
       for Linux,
              sudo apt update
              sudo apt search jdk
              sudo apt search jdk | grep 'openjdk-21'
              sudo apt install -y openjdk-21-jdk  # -y --> yes or no automate
              java --version
    3. Jenkins install on ubuntu ---> Copy the LTS version ---> Paste it in terminal
              sudo systemctl status jenkins
    4. Edit the inbound rule of the VM/EC2
              Add ----> Custome TCP ---> 8080 ---> Save it

    5. Copy PublicIP-address_EC2:8080
    6. sudo cat <path-for-jenkins-password>
    7. paste it in Administrator password
    8. install plugins
    9. In jenkins Web Application,
              Add username and password as a admin and password


        Note:
            systemctl is a linux cmd, system controller is a cmd line tool to control the system services or software services
                control ---> status, stop, start, restart.
            journalctl is to control the logs, where as systemctl is used to control the process
                sudo journalclt -u jenkins
                Default: sudo journalctl #Check system logs itself/ ubuntu os
       
        IMP:
            PORT NO:
              Default:
                    SSH -----> 22
                    HTTP ----> 80
                    HTTPS ---> 443
                    JENKINS -> 8080
              IP Vs Port No
                IP -------> is a connection for a communication in the internet or WWW for a application
                Port No --> is a number that a each software or a application can communicate directly with internet

   
